The ZEVM gateway path is clearer now: for `depositAndCall` it deposits tokens to the target before invoking `onCall`, so the remaining question is whether those deposited assets can short-receive in practice. I’m checking the ZRC20 implementation next because that determines whether the “nominal amount vs actual balance” signal is reportable or too speculative.
