I’ve ruled out the ZEVM “short receipt” part: ZRC20 `deposit()` mints the exact amount to the target before `onCall`, so those receive-side candidates don’t hold there. I’m checking whether the remaining EVM-side issues are genuinely distinct from existing findings or just narrower views of the same reserve-drain bugs.
