> amount`; the function deposits full `msg.value` to the gateway even though the API parameter indicates a smaller amount.","Invoke the swap ETH overload with `fromToken == _ETH_ADDRESS_` and `msg.value > amount`; `_doMixSwap` forwards full `msg.value` to DODO with no contract-side cap or refund of excess."],"round":6,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_reviewer"]},{"id":"F-025","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"GatewayTransferNative refund-claimed event emits zero token/amount due to storage read after delete","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:692","GatewayTransferNative.sol:694","GatewayTransferNative.sol:696","GatewayTransferNative.sol:697"],"claim":"`claimRefund` stores `refundInfo` as a storage pointer, deletes `refundInfos[externalId]`, then emits `EddyCrossChainRefundClaimed` using `refundInfo.token` and `refundInfo.amount` from the deleted slot.","impact":"Off-chain accounting, monitoring, and incident response that rely on the claim event can record zeroed token or amount values, weakening operational controls and reconciliation.","paths":["Execute any successful `claimRefund(externalId)` in `GatewayTransferNative`.","The function transfers funds, deletes the mapping entry, and then reads fields via the stale storage reference for the event.","The event logs zero token or amount despite a real payout."],"round":8,"source_agents":["codex_1","opencode_1"]},{"id":"F-026","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"GatewaySend `onCall` return type is ABI-incompatible with ZetaChain `Callable`","locations":["GatewaySend.sol:344","GatewaySend.sol:385","node_modules/@zetachain/protocol-contracts/contracts/evm/interfaces/IGatewayEVM.sol:229","node_modules/@zetachain/protocol-contracts/contracts/evm/GatewayEVM.sol:439"],"claim":"`GatewaySend.onCall` is declared `returns (bytes4)` and returns `\"\"`, but `IGatewayEVM.Callable.onCall` requires `returns (bytes memory)`. `GatewayEVM` invokes authenticated deliveries via `Callable(destination).onCall(...)`, so the caller ABI-decodes returndata as dynamic bytes and reverts on the fixed-size `bytes4` return payload.","impact":"Authenticated cross-chain deliveries targeting `GatewaySend` cannot complete; the gateway call reverts and the destination settlement path is effectively bricked, forcing failure or refund handling for every attempted delivery.","paths":["A user targets `GatewaySend` as the destination contract for an authenticated cross-chain call.","`GatewayEVM` performs `Callable(destination).onCall(...)` and expects a dynamic `bytes` return.","`GatewaySend.onCall` returns fixed-size `bytes4`; ABI decoding in the gateway reverts, rolling back the entire destination execution."],"round":9,"source_agents":["merge_reviewer"]},{"id":"F-031","severity":"Low","confidence":"high","title":"Same-token WZETA payouts skip unwrap and deliver wrapped tokens instead of native ZETA","locations":["GatewayTransferNative.sol:392","GatewayTransferNative.sol:416"],"claim":"`GatewayTransferNative.onCall` only unwraps WZETA in the swap branch. When the incoming asset is already WZETA and `decoded.targetZRC20 == zrc20`, execution takes the same-token branch and transfers WZETA ERC20 directly instead of unwrapping to native ZETA.","impact":"Receivers that expect native ZETA can receive the wrong asset. EOAs must perform an unexpected unwrap step, while contract recipients without ERC20 handling or recovery logic can end up with unusable or permanently locked funds.","paths":["Bridge or route a native-transfer message into `GatewayTransferNative` with `zrc20 == WZETA` and `decoded.targetZRC20 == WZETA`.","`onCall` enters the same-token branch and sends `amount - platformFeesForTx` of WZETA via ERC20 transfer.","The recipient receives wrapped tokens instead of native ZETA and any downstream logic expecting native value fails or strands the funds."],"round":10,"source_agents":["codex_1","merge_reviewer"]}],"rejected_candidates":[{"title":"Receive-side callbacks spend nominal amounts